<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBFFFB634A0FBF4952F953F" bold="true" box="[199,531,1109,1134]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">
Description. 
<typeStatus id="09388843FFBFFFB63505FBF496F3953F" box="[354,463,1109,1134]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Holotype</typeStatus>
male
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFBFFFB63642FBF49547953F" box="[549,635,1109,1134]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[144,1429,268,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[144,1429,268,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Habitus. 37. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 38. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., holotype ♂; 39. Chvalaea boliviana Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 40. Chvalaea catarinensis Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♂; 41. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov., paratype ♂. 42. Chvalaea masneri Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612725/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Body length: 4.4 mm. Wing length: 4.3 mm. 
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBFFFB630C3FBF493D0953F" bold="true" box="[1188,1260,1109,1134]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Head.</emphasis>
Frons (at midlength narrower than width of anterior ocellus) narrow, as long as 1/4 length of face. Antenna brown, except pedicel yellow; postpedicel about twice length of scape and pedicel combined, with dense brown microtrichia and 1 short, thin dorsal seta near base; stylus arista-like, about 1.5 times length of scape, pedicel and postpedicel combined; 1 pair of ocellar setae very short, proclinate. Proboscis pale brown and very short; palpus yellow covered with dense yellow pruinosity and long and slender setae. 
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBFFFB637D3FAA893289473" bold="true" box="[948,1044,1289,1314]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Thorax.</emphasis>
Covered with yellow pruinosity. Pronotum dark brown. Scutum pale brown, except for broad median stripe, spot on notopleuron and narrow region above notopleuron, both dark brown, postpronotal lobe yellow, postalar callus pale yellow. Pleura brown, except upper margin of anepisternum and laterotergite yellow. Scutellum dark brown (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFBFFFB6306BFAD4937394DF" box="[1036,1103,1397,1422]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,987,1009]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. 5–6. Mediotergite. 5. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, large central black mark highlighted; 6: Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. 7–8. Hind femur. 7. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006; 8. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., black medium ring highlighted. Scale bars: Figs 5–6 = 0.2 mm; Figs 7–8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612709/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) with 1 thin, short lateral seta [1 apical pair of scutellar setae lost, apparently strong]. Mediotergite dark brown (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFBFFFB63012FA38938394E3" box="[1141,1215,1433,1458]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,987,1009]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. 5–6. Mediotergite. 5. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, large central black mark highlighted; 6: Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. 7–8. Hind femur. 7. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006; 8. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., black medium ring highlighted. Scale bars: Figs 5–6 = 0.2 mm; Figs 7–8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612709/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Acrostichals and dorsocentrals uniserial, short, slender and sparse on scutum; notopleuron with 1 long and strong seta, with 5 shorter, more slender setae; 2 anterior postalar setae slender, short and 1 posterior postalar seta [lost in 
<typeStatus id="09388843FFBFFFB63154FA4092A494AB" box="[1331,1432,1505,1530]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">holotype</typeStatus>
, apparently strong]. 
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBFFFB63517F9A4968B974F" bold="true" box="[368,439,1541,1566]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Wing.</emphasis>
Membrane pale brown; pterostigma brown, elongate and narrow; cell dm slightly shorter than basal cells; cell cua slightly shorter than half cell bm; CuA+CuP not reaching wing margin; veins M 
<subScript id="4A0734A4FFBFFFB6315BF99992789717" attach="left" box="[1340,1348,1592,1606]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript id="4A0734A4FFBFFFB631F3F99992A09717" attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1592,1606]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">4</subScript>
not reaching wing margin (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFBFFFB635AEF9F195229738" box="[457,542,1616,1641]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–52" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1529,1551]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,447,1507]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 45–52. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Wings. 45. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 46. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., holotype ♂; 47. Chvalaea boliviana Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 48. Chvalaea catarinensis Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♂; 49. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov., paratype ♂; 50. Chvalaea masneri Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 51. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 52. Chvalaea sinclairi sp. nov., holotype ♂. Abbreviations: bm = basal medial cell; br = basal radial cell; cua = anterior cubital cell; CuA+CuP = anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm = discal medial cell; M 1 = first branch of media; M 4 = fourth branch of media; R 1 = anterior branch of radius; R 2+3 = second branch of radius; R 4+5 = third branch of radius. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612729/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBFFFB63655F9F1954D9738" bold="true" box="[562,625,1616,1641]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Legs.</emphasis>
All coxae whitish yellow except basal 2/3 of fore coxa brown; fore and mid femora pale brown except for black extreme apex, hind femur slightly clavate, whitish yellow on basal third, with wide black ring medially, yellow apically with narrow, black ring at extreme apex (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFBFFFB630F9F93993DA97E0" box="[1182,1254,1688,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,987,1009]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,193,965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. 5–6. Mediotergite. 5. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, large central black mark highlighted; 6: Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. 7–8. Hind femur. 7. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006; 8. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., black medium ring highlighted. Scale bars: Figs 5–6 = 0.2 mm; Figs 7–8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612709/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); all tibiae pale brown, except hind tibia black; fore and mid tarsomere 1 whitish, remaining fore and mid tarsomeres pale yellow, hind tarsomere 1–2 whitish, remaining hind tarsomeres dark brown. Chaetotaxy: fore femur without highlighted setae, mid femur with 1 long and slender anterodorsal setae near apex, hind femur with 2 anteroventral at midlength and 1 anterodorsal apical seta; fore tibia with 1 long and thin posteroventral seta at mid-length, mid tibia with 1 long and thick dorsal seta near base, 2 anterior setae on basal half and 1 anterior on apical half, 1 long ventral seta near mid-length, hind tibia without outstanding setae; fore and mid tarsomere 1 with 1 ventral seta stronger and long near base; hind tarsomere 1 with 2 series of rows of elongate black spine-like setae, including 4 anteroventrals and 3 posteroventrals, fore and mid tarsomeres 3–4 and hind tarsomeres 3–5 with short, blunt, black spine-like ventral setae. 
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBFFFB635CBF87D951496A4" bold="true" box="[428,552,2012,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="350">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Black, slender, slightly curved upwards, sides almost parallel-sided in lateral view. 
<typeStatus id="09388843FFB8FFB134BAFF36967991E1" box="[221,325,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Holotype</typeStatus>
male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB8FFB13670FF3695A391E1" box="[535,671,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,193,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. Male terminalia (Holotype), phallus highlighted in gray. 23. Hypandrium and epandrium, ventral view; 24. Epandrium with cerci, dorsal view; 25. Hypandrium and epandrium, left lateral view; 26. Hypandrium and epandrium, right lateral view. Abbreviations: bac scl = bacilliform sclerite; sur = surstylus; cerc = cercus; ep = epandrium; hypd = hypandrium; subep s = subepandrial sclerite; ph = phallus; hyp = hypoproct. Scale bars = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612719/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Figs 23–26</figureCitation>
): hypandrium narrow, elongate and oval, about twice longer than wide, apical margin slightly convex with 2 subapical long setae (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB8FFB137FAFF1D94CA9185" box="[925,1014,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,193,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. Male terminalia (Holotype), phallus highlighted in gray. 23. Hypandrium and epandrium, ventral view; 24. Epandrium with cerci, dorsal view; 25. Hypandrium and epandrium, left lateral view; 26. Hypandrium and epandrium, right lateral view. Abbreviations: bac scl = bacilliform sclerite; sur = surstylus; cerc = cercus; ep = epandrium; hypd = hypandrium; subep s = subepandrial sclerite; ph = phallus; hyp = hypoproct. Scale bars = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612719/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
); subepandrial sclerite with anterior margin rounded and apical margin truncate; hypoproct with apex truncate and lateral margin round, triangular indentation in middle of basal margin (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB8FFB1362DFEA595A3904D" box="[586,671,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,193,1257]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1279]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov. Male terminalia (Holotype), phallus highlighted in gray. 23. Hypandrium and epandrium, ventral view; 24. Epandrium with cerci, dorsal view; 25. Hypandrium and epandrium, left lateral view; 26. Hypandrium and epandrium, right lateral view. Abbreviations: bac scl = bacilliform sclerite; sur = surstylus; cerc = cercus; ep = epandrium; hypd = hypandrium; subep s = subepandrial sclerite; ph = phallus; hyp = hypoproct. Scale bars = 0.3 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612719/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D63C36E1FFB8FFB134A0FE86969E9011" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[199,418,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
