<subSubSection id="9E99656AFFB8FFB134A0F9D7926C97DE" box="[199,1360,1654,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D63C36E1FFB8FFB134A0F9D7926C97DE" blockId="4.[151,1437,1654,1935]" box="[199,1360,1654,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB134A0F9D7967297DE" bold="true" box="[199,334,1654,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13664F9D6956097DE" box="[515,604,1655,1679]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">annulus</emphasis>
= ring, in reference to the contrasting black ring on the hind femur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E99656AFFB8FFB134A0F93A941296DF" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D63C36E1FFB8FFB134A0F93A941296DF" blockId="4.[151,1437,1654,1935]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB134A0F93A960797E5" bold="true" box="[199,315,1691,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFB8FFB13525F93A951C97E2" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,544,1691,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13525F93A951C97E2" box="[322,544,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Chvalaea annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB1364FF93A95BE97E5" bold="true" box="[552,642,1691,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFB8FFB1364FF93A95BE97E5" box="[552,642,1691,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFB8FFB13771F93A94B297E2" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[790,910,1691,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13771F93A94B297E2" box="[790,910,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a broad median stripe, spot on the notopleuron and narrow region above notopleuron, both dark brown, veins M 
<subScript id="4A0734A4FFB8FFB13023F96F9370978D" attach="left" box="[1092,1100,1742,1756]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript id="4A0734A4FFB8FFB130FCF96F939F978D" attach="left" box="[1179,1187,1742,1756]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">4</subScript>
not reaching the wing margin, and fore and mid tarsomeres 3–4 and hind tarsomeres 3–5 with short, blunt, black ventral spine-like setae. In 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFB8FFB134DFF8AB967B9673" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[184,327,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB134DFF8AB967B9673" box="[184,327,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13535F8A896939673" bold="true" box="[338,431,1801,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFB8FFB13535F8A896939673" box="[338,431,1801,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the pronotum, scutellum and mediotergite are dark brown, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFB8FFB13093F8AB92539673" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[1268,1391,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13093F8AB92539673" box="[1268,1391,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pronotum and scutellum are yellow and the mediotergite is yellow with a black spot. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFB8FFB13083F88F924E9617" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[1252,1394,1838,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13083F88F924E9617" box="[1252,1394,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB1311DF88C97F4963B" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFB8FFB1311DF88C97F4963B" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the hind femur slightly clavate with a wide black ring medially; in 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFB8FFB13792F8F39352963B" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[1013,1134,1874,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB8FFB13792F8F39352963B" box="[1013,1134,1874,1898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">C. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the hind femur is strongly clavate, yellow with a very narrow, dark brown apical ring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
